	   <tr><td colspan=2>Camped this on Saturday as a level 30 shammie.&nbsp;&nbsp;This is a very easy camp, but very long and boring.  There is a two spawn that is right past the first gate on the left.  It is in a room behind a rock.  If you are a Barbarian like myself you have to shrink to get in there.  I needed another person to break the room up at level 30.  The alchemist is a rare spawn and you normally have to kill place holder for him to spawn.  The room consists normally of a caster of some sort and a regular ice goblin.  The tactic I used was to invis all the way to the door.  I buffed with all resists and normal strength etc.  Saturday I broke the spawn with a guild mate and the leggings dropped after four hours and the cloak dropped after six.  Held the room for another 5 hours and the alchemist didn't even show.  Being I still needed one I went back on Sunday with a friend.  He was a level 31 shammie as well.  The room is very small and there are three additional casters outside.  When you first break the spawn you need to root the mobs so they don't run outside and get help.  If they do don't worry with sow I made it out alive.  Getting back to Sunday I rolled up in there and saw the alchemist was actually there as a first spawn.  Me and my friend broke it with ease and got the cloak.  We then gated out and rolled.  He won the cloak.  Since it is a slow spawn rate about 25 minutes you can hold the room yourself at level 30.  I could get FM and keep myself buffed with this kind of time and without clarity.  I went back to the room and 25 minutes later the alchemist popped again I was very surprised.  Needless to say after about 3 casts of my DD and root he was dead.  Pretty easy if you ask me.  The beautiful thing was he dropped a second cape.  Don't know what the odds are or if it was becuase I gated out and then returned, but I had some great luck.<br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
